        <num>131.175</num>
        <content>
          <p>Notwithstanding any other provisions of KRS Chapters 131 to 143A, for all taxes payable directly to the Department of Revenue, the sheriff or the county clerk, the commissioner shall have authority to waive the penalty, but not interest, where it is shown to the satisfaction of the department that failure to file or pay timely is due to reasonable cause. For purposes of this section, any addition to tax provided in  and shall be considered as penalty.</p>
